<paragraph blockId="12.[151,1437,1378,1908]" pageId="12" pageNumber="473">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,1378,1404]" pageId="12" pageNumber="473">Remarks.</emphasis>
The spicules of our specimen are a close match in terms of size and form to the 
<typeStatus box="[1272,1320,1378,1404]" pageId="12" pageNumber="473">type</typeStatus>
specimen (spicules measurements from 
<typeStatus box="[484,536,1414,1440]" pageId="12" pageNumber="473">type</typeStatus>
: styles 398(439)473 by 10(15)18μm, tylotes 212(234)248 by 8(11)14 μm, chelae 17(20)24 μm). 
<bibRefCitation author="Topsent, E." box="[322,492,1450,1476]" pageId="12" pageNumber="473" pagination="69 - 76" refId="ref37649" refString="Topsent, E. (1907) Poecilosclerides nouvelles recueillies par le Francais dans l'Antarctique. Bulletin du Museum national d'histoire naturelle, Paris, 13, 69 - 76. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. part. 4486" type="journal article" year="1907">Topsent (1907)</bibRefCitation>
does not record bipocilla as being present in the species description and we did not find them in our specimens or on re-examining slides of the 
<typeStatus box="[848,900,1486,1512]" pageId="12" pageNumber="473">type</typeStatus>
. However, 
<bibRefCitation author="Rios, P." box="[1029,1164,1486,1513]" pageId="12" pageNumber="473" refId="ref36627" refString="Rios, P. (2006) Esponjas del orden Poecilosclerida de las campanas espanolas de bentos Antartico. Unpublished PhD Thesis, University of Santiago de Compostela, Santiago de Compostela, 527 pp." type="book" year="2006">Rios (2006)</bibRefCitation>
made new preparations from the 
<typeStatus box="[254,302,1522,1548]" pageId="12" pageNumber="473">type</typeStatus>
specimen and found them to be common. 
<bibRefCitation author="Goodwin, C. &amp; Brewin, P. E. &amp; Brickle, P." box="[780,1030,1522,1548]" pageId="12" pageNumber="473" pagination="1 - 48" refId="ref35020" refString="Goodwin, C., Brewin, P. E. &amp; Brickle, P. (2012) Sponge biodiversity of South Georgia island with descriptions of fifteen new species. Zootaxa, 3542, 1 - 48. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 3542.1.1" type="journal article" year="2012">
Goodwin 
<emphasis box="[892,948,1522,1548]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="473">et al.</emphasis>
(2012)
</bibRefCitation>
also noted bipocilla to be present in specimens they ascribed to this species which were collected from 
<collectingCountry box="[897,1062,1558,1584]" name="South Georgia and the South Sandwich Islands" pageId="12" pageNumber="473">South Georgia</collectingCountry>
. It is possible the species actually represents a species complex. However, 
<bibRefCitation author="Desqueyroux-Faundez, R. &amp; van Soest, R. W. M." box="[606,1088,1594,1621]" pageId="12" pageNumber="473" pagination="3 - 79" refId="ref34849" refString="Desqueyroux-Faundez, R. &amp; van Soest, R. W. M. (1996) A review of Iophonidae, Myxillidae and Tedaniidae occurring in the South East Pacific (Porifera: Poecilosclerida). Revue suisse de Zoologie, 103, 3 - 79. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. part. 79938" type="journal article" year="1996">Desqueyroux-Faúndez &amp; Van Soest (1996)</bibRefCitation>
do not consider bipocilla to be a reliable character for species differentiation in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Gray" authorityYear="1867" box="[698,777,1630,1656]" class="Demospongiae" family="Acarnidae" genus="Iophon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Poecilosclerida" pageId="12" pageNumber="473" phylum="Porifera" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[698,777,1630,1656]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="473">Iophon</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as their presence can vary in different specimens from the same species.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="12.[151,1437,1378,1908]" pageId="12" pageNumber="473">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,353,1701,1728]" pageId="12" pageNumber="473">Distribution.</emphasis>
The 
<typeStatus box="[410,458,1702,1728]" pageId="12" pageNumber="473">type</typeStatus>
locality is Île Anvers (Anvers Island) on the Antarctic Peninsula. The species is widely distributed in the Antarctic and sub-Antarctic with records from Bransfield Strait, Bellinghausen Sea, Ross Sea, Kerguelen Island, South 
<collectingCountry box="[441,618,1774,1800]" name="United Kingdom" pageId="12" pageNumber="473">Orkney Islands</collectingCountry>
, South 
<collectingRegion box="[709,900,1774,1800]" country="United Kingdom" name="Shetland Islands" pageId="12" pageNumber="473">Shetland Islands</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[915,1082,1774,1800]" name="South Georgia and the South Sandwich Islands" pageId="12" pageNumber="473">South Georgia</collectingCountry>
and Weddell Sea (
<bibRefCitation author="Kirkpatrick, R." pageId="12" pageNumber="473" pagination="1 - 56" refId="ref35564" refString="Kirkpatrick, R. (1908) Porifera (Sponges). II. Tetraxonida. National Antarctic Expedition, 1901 - 1904. Natural History, 4, 1 - 56." type="journal article" year="1908">Kirkpatrick 1908</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Topsent, E." box="[225,383,1810,1836]" pageId="12" pageNumber="473" pagination="579 - 643" refId="ref37727" refString="Topsent, E. (1913) Spongiaires de l'Expedition Antarctique Nationale Ecossaise. Transactions of the Royal Society of Edinburgh, 49, 579 - 643. https: // doi. org / 10.1017 / S 0080456800013119" type="journal article" year="1913">Topsent 1913</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Topsent, E." box="[398,457,1810,1836]" pageId="12" pageNumber="473" pagination="1 - 88" refId="ref37835" refString="Topsent, E. (1917) Spongiaires. In: Joubin, L. (Ed.), Deuxieme Expedition Antarctique Francaise (1908 - 1910) Commandee par le Dr. Jean Charcot. Sciences Physiques: Documents Scientifiques. Masson &amp; Cie, Paris, pp. 1 - 88." type="book chapter" year="1917">1917</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Hentschel, E." box="[473,654,1810,1836]" pageId="12" pageNumber="473" pagination="35 - 141" refId="ref35188" refString="Hentschel, E. (1914) Monaxone Kieselschwamme und Hornschwamme der Deutschen Sudpolar-Expedition 1901 - 1903. Deutsche Sudpolar-Expedition, 1901 - 03, 15, 35 - 141." type="journal article" year="1914">Hentschel 1914</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Desqueyroux-Faundez, R." box="[670,993,1810,1836]" pageId="12" pageNumber="473" pagination="97 - 158" refId="ref34821" refString="Desqueyroux-Faundez, R. (1989) Demospongiae (Porifera) del litoral chileno antartico. Series Cientia Instituto Antartico Chileno, 39, 97 - 158." type="journal article" year="1989">Desqueyroux-Faúndez 1989</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Pansini, M. &amp; Calcinai, B. &amp; Cattaneo-Vietti, R. &amp; Sara, M." box="[1009,1231,1810,1836]" pageId="12" pageNumber="473" pagination="67 - 100" refId="ref36291" refString="Pansini, M., Calcinai, B., Cattaneo-Vietti, R. &amp; Sara, M. (1994) Demosponges from Terra Nova Bay (Ross Sea, Antarctica): 1987 / 1988 and 1989 / 90. Programma Nazionale di Ricerche in Antartide, Expeditions. National Scientific Commission for Antarctica Oceanographic Campaign 1987 / 88 and 1989 / 90, 3, 67 - 100." type="journal article" year="1994">
Pansini 
<emphasis box="[1102,1162,1810,1836]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="473">et al.</emphasis>
1994
</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Gutt, J. &amp; Koltun, V. M." pageId="12" pageNumber="473" pagination="227 - 234" refId="ref35072" refString="Gutt, J. &amp; Koltun, V. M. (1995) Sponges of the Lazarev and Weddell Sea, Antarctica: explanations for their patchy occurrence. Antarctic Science, 7, 227 - 234. https: // doi. org / 10.1017 / S 0954102095000320" type="journal article" year="1995">Gutt and Koltun 1995</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Rios, P." box="[222,340,1846,1872]" pageId="12" pageNumber="473" refId="ref36627" refString="Rios, P. (2006) Esponjas del orden Poecilosclerida de las campanas espanolas de bentos Antartico. Unpublished PhD Thesis, University of Santiago de Compostela, Santiago de Compostela, 527 pp." type="book" year="2006">Rios 2006</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Goodwin, C. &amp; Brewin, P. E. &amp; Brickle, P." box="[350,584,1846,1872]" pageId="12" pageNumber="473" pagination="1 - 48" refId="ref35020" refString="Goodwin, C., Brewin, P. E. &amp; Brickle, P. (2012) Sponge biodiversity of South Georgia island with descriptions of fifteen new species. Zootaxa, 3542, 1 - 48. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 3542.1.1" type="journal article" year="2012">
Goodwin 
<emphasis box="[461,517,1846,1872]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="473">et al.</emphasis>
2012
</bibRefCitation>
). 
<bibRefCitation author="Burton, M." box="[602,761,1846,1872]" pageId="12" pageNumber="473" pagination="393 - 458" refId="ref34303" refString="Burton, M. (1929) British Antarctic (' Terra Nova') Expedition, 1910. Natural History Report. Porifera: Part II: Antarctic Sponges. Zoology, 6, 393 - 458." type="journal article" year="1929">Burton (1929)</bibRefCitation>
considered the majority of Antarctic species of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Gray" authorityYear="1867" box="[1295,1374,1846,1872]" class="Demospongiae" family="Acarnidae" genus="Iophon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Poecilosclerida" pageId="12" pageNumber="473" phylum="Porifera" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1295,1374,1846,1872]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="473">Iophon</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
to be synonyms so it is not clear if his specimens include this species.
</paragraph>
